==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sheathed
<hw>Sheathed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Povided
with, or inclosed in, sheath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Invested by a sheath, or
cylindrical membranaceous tube, which is the base of the leaf, as the
stalk or culm in grasses; vaginate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sheather</ent>⟦br⟧
